main event: A civilian reported observing bright round lights in the sky every night over Manchester, Pennsylvania in June 1967.
interesting points: The report mentions that the lights seemed to stay in the same position against the background of stars., The witness described the lights as being bright and moving slowly in a defined pattern., Handwritten notes indicate the witness attempted to create a crude map to detail their observations., The document includes a request from the Air Force for additional information to aid in analysis., The conclusion of the investigation was that there was insufficient data for evaluation.
sighted object: bright round lights in the sky
witness description: A civilian observing lights in the sky.
